WEBVTT

00:00:29.623 --> 00:00:32.103
Welcome to the Ocean Studio here of the

00:00:32.264 --> 00:00:33.424
Yahowah Vlog.

00:00:33.585 --> 00:00:34.865
I am your host, Craig Winn,

00:00:34.886 --> 00:00:36.906
and this handsome fellow here,

00:00:36.966 --> 00:00:38.146
this is Wookie.

00:00:38.948 --> 00:00:42.128
We're going to start a whole series of

00:00:42.950 --> 00:00:43.310
Mizmowr

00:00:43.909 --> 00:00:45.871
Four more are on the agenda.

00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:48.893
They really flow right out of the first

00:00:49.033 --> 00:00:51.713
eleven that Dowd revealed.

00:00:52.835 --> 00:00:52.935
And

00:00:54.204 --> 00:00:54.584
In them,

00:00:54.624 --> 00:00:57.927
we are being afforded a choice between

00:00:58.487 --> 00:01:00.270
siding with the family of God,

00:01:00.310 --> 00:01:01.850
that would be the Beryth Covenant,

00:01:02.392 --> 00:01:04.453
or the institutions of man,

00:01:04.493 --> 00:01:06.295
that would be religion and politics,

00:01:06.375 --> 00:01:08.516
conspiracy, militarism,

00:01:08.677 --> 00:01:10.299
that sort of thing.

00:01:10.379 --> 00:01:13.742
Dowd wants to provide the information that

00:01:13.781 --> 00:01:16.183
we need so that we're equipped to make

00:01:16.263 --> 00:01:18.746
an informed and rational decision.

00:01:19.656 --> 00:01:21.376
Now, considering what follows,

00:01:21.796 --> 00:01:24.298
I think this is a fine way to

00:01:24.438 --> 00:01:25.578
introduce this psalm,

00:01:25.599 --> 00:01:28.019
which is really consistent with the others

00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:29.680
that we have seen previously.

00:01:29.739 --> 00:01:32.462
It reads to the enduring leader.

00:01:33.162 --> 00:01:36.963
It is La ha natsach to approach and on

00:01:37.004 --> 00:01:39.364
behalf of the everlasting and majestic

00:01:39.405 --> 00:01:42.126
director who endeavors to guide and who is

00:01:42.186 --> 00:01:43.506
preeminent and distinguished,

00:01:43.546 --> 00:01:44.626
even glorious forever.

00:01:45.805 --> 00:01:49.628
And the interesting factor is that natsach

00:01:49.748 --> 00:01:51.789
is a verb and it's modified by the

00:01:51.828 --> 00:01:55.471
appeal participle and the masculine

00:01:55.531 --> 00:01:56.091
singular.

00:01:56.132 --> 00:01:59.054
The appeal means that it causes the

00:01:59.814 --> 00:02:00.215
object,

00:02:00.234 --> 00:02:02.016
the subject causes the object to

00:02:02.075 --> 00:02:04.298
participate in the action,

00:02:04.337 --> 00:02:08.760
which is leadership and enabling them to

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:09.281
approach.

00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:12.342
And the participle makes it a verbal noun

00:02:12.402 --> 00:02:12.903
so that

00:02:14.104 --> 00:02:17.645
The verb is also manifest as a title.

00:02:18.724 --> 00:02:20.585
So it's a really interesting way of

00:02:21.286 --> 00:02:26.086
conveying a dedication really to a Mizmowr

00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:26.687
or psalm.

00:02:28.606 --> 00:02:31.407
So it is to the enduring leader above

00:02:31.448 --> 00:02:34.388
and beyond the eighth octave.

00:02:36.368 --> 00:02:39.889
It's a scale for eternity, if you will,

00:02:39.949 --> 00:02:41.550
for heaven and beyond.

00:02:42.468 --> 00:02:47.592
For shamynyth and shamynyth,

00:02:48.151 --> 00:02:50.453
they are shamyny and Shamaym.

00:02:51.054 --> 00:02:54.675
They are eight and infinite in time and

00:02:54.735 --> 00:02:55.895
the spiritual realm.

00:02:56.056 --> 00:02:58.737
It is an integration between those

00:02:58.777 --> 00:02:59.358
concepts.

00:02:59.679 --> 00:03:03.080
A song, a Mizmowr of Dowd,

00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:05.481
whose name means beloved.

00:03:06.201 --> 00:03:09.403
This is Mizmowr lyric to sing Psalm twelve

00:03:09.604 --> 00:03:10.645
in its dedication.

00:03:11.669 --> 00:03:11.750
Well,

00:03:11.789 --> 00:03:15.331
this is the second of three occasions

00:03:15.391 --> 00:03:20.155
where a shamynyth appears in the text

00:03:20.215 --> 00:03:23.037
in reference to instrumentation or a song.

00:03:23.836 --> 00:03:27.179
Closely related to shamynyth,

00:03:27.739 --> 00:03:28.379
it should be

00:03:29.633 --> 00:03:30.813
It would be, anyway,

00:03:30.873 --> 00:03:34.956
natural to consider shamynyth to be the

00:03:35.176 --> 00:03:36.198
eighth octave,

00:03:37.498 --> 00:03:40.401
as the English term octave is based upon

00:03:40.442 --> 00:03:43.283
the Latin word for eight, or octo.

00:03:44.465 --> 00:03:46.286
The only problem with this approach is

00:03:46.346 --> 00:03:49.268
that a harp can only play six and

00:03:49.328 --> 00:03:51.288
a half octaves, not eight,

00:03:52.049 --> 00:03:54.890
and the range exceeds other stringed

00:03:54.950 --> 00:03:55.491
instruments.

00:03:56.091 --> 00:03:56.491
Further,

00:03:57.192 --> 00:03:59.552
this is a song the human voice is

00:03:59.693 --> 00:04:03.014
only capable of performing within a four

00:04:03.215 --> 00:04:04.355
octave range,

00:04:04.395 --> 00:04:06.937
with the eighth octave residing at the

00:04:07.056 --> 00:04:10.058
upward limit of what people can even hear.

00:04:11.328 --> 00:04:13.109
So it's interesting, nevertheless,

00:04:13.188 --> 00:04:17.891
that sheep, and God loves His sheep,

00:04:19.033 --> 00:04:22.233
can hear well into the eighth octave,

00:04:22.795 --> 00:04:25.036
but that makes them quite unique in this

00:04:25.096 --> 00:04:25.536
regard.

00:04:26.697 --> 00:04:27.937
In context, however,

00:04:28.057 --> 00:04:30.959
when we consider a scale based upon eight

00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:32.980
in harmony with Yahowah's nomenclature,

00:04:33.461 --> 00:04:35.482
we're led to several thought-provoking

00:04:35.521 --> 00:04:36.322
possibilities.

00:04:37.101 --> 00:04:40.124
As we discussed in previous programs,

00:04:40.163 --> 00:04:43.666
the eighth day of Sukah serves as a

00:04:43.766 --> 00:04:46.189
reference to eternal life.

00:04:47.228 --> 00:04:50.391
And this would be spent with God in

00:04:50.432 --> 00:04:52.632
heaven, which is in the seventh dimension.

00:04:52.673 --> 00:04:54.033
But the seventh dimension,

00:04:54.574 --> 00:04:55.995
replete with all time,

00:04:56.036 --> 00:04:58.076
could be considered the eighth octave.

00:04:58.838 --> 00:05:00.899
Further, the Hebrew word for eight,

00:05:01.459 --> 00:05:05.201
shamyny, is remarkably similar to Shamaym,

00:05:06.083 --> 00:05:06.283
heaven.

00:05:07.711 --> 00:05:11.692
And what God is offering us is sort

00:05:11.733 --> 00:05:13.812
of interesting here when you put it all

00:05:13.853 --> 00:05:14.473
in perspective.

00:05:16.394 --> 00:05:21.194
We were given a Neshama to make man,

00:05:21.495 --> 00:05:22.134
men and women,

00:05:23.055 --> 00:05:25.815
more capable of relating to and engaging

00:05:25.875 --> 00:05:29.475
with God when he offered us a Neshamah,

00:05:29.675 --> 00:05:30.437
a conscience,

00:05:30.697 --> 00:05:34.838
in addition to the Nepesh or souls that

00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:36.817
permeated all other things.

00:05:37.757 --> 00:05:43.100
And so with us having a Neshamah,

00:05:43.620 --> 00:05:46.382
we could think our way to God,

00:05:46.862 --> 00:05:48.523
which is unique.

00:05:49.524 --> 00:05:52.665
And unfortunately,

00:05:52.985 --> 00:05:55.266
the first men and women, Adam,

00:05:55.387 --> 00:05:56.127
man and woman,

00:05:56.968 --> 00:06:00.389
