00:12:51.735 --> 00:12:53.197
I have said this so many times,

00:12:53.236 --> 00:12:54.697
but it always bears repeating.

00:12:55.278 --> 00:12:58.519
Yahowah is an accurate transliteration of

00:12:58.559 --> 00:13:00.461
the name of Elowah, God,

00:13:00.941 --> 00:13:02.802
guided by His Towrah.

00:13:03.666 --> 00:13:06.206
instructions regarding His Hayah,

00:13:06.647 --> 00:13:09.989
existence, and our Shalowm, reconciliation.

00:13:10.908 --> 00:13:11.928
In those words,

00:13:12.490 --> 00:13:16.171
you have ample proof of the pronunciation

00:13:16.211 --> 00:13:16.912
of God's name.

00:13:16.932 --> 00:13:18.251
It is based on the verb Hayah,

00:13:18.292 --> 00:13:18.912
to exist.

00:13:19.552 --> 00:13:20.952
It tells you how to pronounce three of

00:13:20.993 --> 00:13:21.714
the four letters.

00:13:22.313 --> 00:13:27.855
And Elowah and Shalowm and Towrah all derive

00:13:27.895 --> 00:13:30.456
the O sound from the Hebrew, wah.

00:13:31.238 --> 00:13:32.057
Mystery solved.

00:13:33.153 --> 00:13:36.818
You and I concur in choosing to save.

00:13:36.999 --> 00:13:37.418
Yasa.

00:13:37.519 --> 00:13:41.163
Yasa is the Hebrew verb that depicts

00:13:41.283 --> 00:13:45.249
deliverance, emancipation, salvation,

00:13:46.090 --> 00:13:47.030
all of these things.

00:13:47.091 --> 00:13:48.173
It is a

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:52.005
Collection here of desires.

